verses.text_plain: Now there was a certain man of Ramathaim–zophim, of mount Ephraim, and his name was Elkanah, the son of Jeroham, the son of Elihu, the son of Tohu, the son of Zuph, an Ephrathite:
verses.verse_html: 1Now there was a certain man of Ramathaim–zophim, of mount Ephraim, and his name was Elkanah, the son of Jeroham, the son of Elihu, the son of Tohu, the son of Zuph, an Ephrathite:

verses.text_plain: And he had two wives; the name of the one was Hannah, and the name of the other Peninnah: and Peninnah had children, but Hannah had no children.
verses.verse_html: 2And he had two wives; the name of the one was Hannah, and the name of the other Peninnah: and Peninnah had children, but Hannah had no children.

verses.text_plain: And this man went up out of his city yearly to worship and to sacrifice unto the Lord of hosts in Shiloh. And the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, the priests of the Lord, were there.
verses.verse_html:
3And this man went up out of his city yearly to worship and to sacrifice unto the Lord of hosts in Shiloh. And the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, the priests of the Lord, were there. ▼
▼ yearly: Heb. from year to year

footnotes.body_text: ▼ yearly: Heb. from year to year
footnotes.body_html: ▼ yearly: Heb. from year to year

verses.text_plain: And when the time was that Elkanah offered, he gave to Peninnah his wife, and to all her sons and her daughters, portions:
verses.verse_html: 4And when the time was that Elkanah offered, he gave to Peninnah his wife, and to all her sons and her daughters, portions:

verses.text_plain: But unto Hannah he gave a worthy portion; for he loved Hannah: but the Lord had shut up her womb.
verses.verse_html:
5But unto Hannah he gave a worthy portion; for he loved Hannah: but the Lord had shut up her womb. ▼
▼ worthy: or, double

verses.text_plain: And her adversary also provoked her sore, for to make her fret, because the Lord had shut up her womb.
verses.verse_html:
6And her adversary also provoked her sore, for to make her fret, because the Lord had shut up her womb. ▼
▼ provoked: Heb. angered

verses.text_plain: And as he did so year by year, when she went up to the house of the Lord, so she provoked her; therefore she wept, and did not eat.
verses.verse_html:
7And as he did so year by year, when she went up to the house of the Lord, so she provoked her; therefore she wept, and did not eat. ▼
▼ when…: or, from the time that she, etc: Heb. from her going up

footnotes.body_text: ▼ when…: or, from the time that she, etc: Heb. from her going up
footnotes.body_html: ▼ when…: or, from the time that she, etc: Heb. from her going up

verses.text_plain: Then said Elkanah her husband to her, Hannah, why weepest thou? and why eatest thou not? and why is thy heart grieved? am not I better to thee than ten sons?
verses.verse_html: 8Then said Elkanah her husband to her, Hannah, why weepest thou? and why eatest thou not? and why is thy heart grieved? am not I better to thee than ten sons?

tokens.text: thou not? and why is thy heart

verses.text_plain: So Hannah rose up after they had eaten in Shiloh, and after they had drunk. Now Eli the priest sat upon a seat by a post of the temple of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 9So Hannah rose up after they had eaten in Shiloh, and after they had drunk. Now Eli the priest sat upon a seat by a post of the temple of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And she was in bitterness of soul, and prayed unto the Lord, and wept sore.
verses.verse_html:
10And she was in bitterness of soul, and prayed unto the Lord, and wept sore. ▼
▼ in…: Heb. bitter of soul

footnotes.body_html: ▼ in…: Heb. bitter of soul

verses.text_plain: And she vowed a vow, and said, O Lord of hosts, if thou wilt indeed look on the affliction of thine handmaid, and remember me, and not forget thine handmaid, but wilt give unto thine handmaid a man child, then I will give him unto the Lord all the days of his life, and there shall no razor come upon his head.
verses.verse_html:
11And she vowed a vow, and said, O Lord of hosts, if thou wilt indeed look on the affliction of thine handmaid, and remember me, and not forget thine handmaid, but wilt give unto thine handmaid a man child, then I will give him unto the Lord all the days of his life, and there shall no razor come upon his head. ▼
▼ a man…: Heb. seed of men

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a man…: Heb. seed of men
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a man…: Heb. seed of men

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass, as she continued praying before the Lord, that Eli marked her mouth.
verses.verse_html:
12And it came to pass, as she continued praying before the Lord, that Eli marked her mouth. ▼
▼ continued…: Heb. multiplied to pray

tokens.text: And it came to pass, as she continued

footnotes.body_html: ▼ continued…: Heb. multiplied to pray

verses.text_plain: Now Hannah, she spake in her heart; only her lips moved, but her voice was not heard: therefore Eli thought she had been drunken.
verses.verse_html: 13Now Hannah, she spake in her heart; only her lips moved, but her voice was not heard: therefore Eli thought she had been drunken.

verses.text_plain: And Eli said unto her, How long wilt thou be drunken? put away thy wine from thee.
verses.verse_html: 14And Eli said unto her, How long wilt thou be drunken? put away thy wine from thee.

tokens.text: unto her, How long wilt thou be drunken

verses.text_plain: And Hannah answered and said, No, my lord, I am a woman of a sorrowful spirit: I have drunk neither wine nor strong drink, but have poured out my soul before the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
15And Hannah answered and said, No, my lord, I am a woman of a sorrowful spirit: I have drunk neither wine nor strong drink, but have poured out my soul before the Lord. ▼
▼ of a sorrowful…: Heb. hard of spirit

footnotes.body_text: ▼ of a sorrowful…: Heb. hard of spirit
footnotes.body_html: ▼ of a sorrowful…: Heb. hard of spirit

verses.text_plain: Count not thine handmaid for a daughter of Belial: for out of the abundance of my complaint and grief have I spoken hitherto.
verses.verse_html:
16Count not thine handmaid for a daughter of Belial: for out of the abundance of my complaint and grief have I spoken hitherto. ▼
▼ complaint: or, meditation

verses.text_plain: Then Eli answered and said, Go in peace: and the God of Israel grant thee thy petition that thou hast asked of him.
verses.verse_html: 17Then Eli answered and said, Go in peace: and the God of Israel grant thee thy petition that thou hast asked of him.

verses.text_plain: And she said, Let thine handmaid find grace in thy sight. So the woman went her way, and did eat, and her countenance was no more sad.
verses.verse_html: 18And she said, Let thine handmaid find grace in thy sight. So the woman went her way, and did eat, and her countenance was no more sad.

verses.text_plain: And they rose up in the morning early, and worshipped before the Lord, and returned, and came to their house to Ramah: and Elkanah knew Hannah his wife; and the Lord remembered her.
verses.verse_html: 19And they rose up in the morning early, and worshipped before the Lord, and returned, and came to their house to Ramah: and Elkanah knew Hannah his wife; and the Lord remembered her.

verses.text_plain: Wherefore it came to pass, when the time was come about after Hannah had conceived, that she bare a son, and called his name Samuel, saying, Because I have asked him of the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
20Wherefore it came to pass, when the time was come about after Hannah had conceived, that she bare a son, and called his name Samuel, saying, Because I have asked him of the Lord. ▼
▼ when…: Heb. in revolution of days
 , ▼
▼ Samuel: that is, Asked of God

tokens.text: Wherefore it came to pass, when the time

footnotes.body_text: ▼ when…: Heb. in revolution of days
footnotes.body_html: ▼ when…: Heb. in revolution of days

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Samuel: that is, Asked of God
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Samuel: that is, Asked of God

verses.text_plain: And the man Elkanah, and all his house, went up to offer unto the Lord the yearly sacrifice, and his vow.
verses.verse_html: 21And the man Elkanah, and all his house, went up to offer unto the Lord the yearly sacrifice, and his vow.

verses.text_plain: But Hannah went not up; for she said unto her husband, I will not go up until the child be weaned, and then I will bring him, that he may appear before the Lord, and there abide for ever.
verses.verse_html: 22But Hannah went not up; for she said unto her husband, I will not go up until the child be weaned, and then I will bring him, that he may appear before the Lord, and there abide for ever.

verses.text_plain: And Elkanah her husband said unto her, Do what seemeth thee good; tarry until thou have weaned him; only the Lord establish his word. So the woman abode, and gave her son suck until she weaned him.
verses.verse_html: 23And Elkanah her husband said unto her, Do what seemeth thee good; tarry until thou have weaned him; only the Lord establish his word. So the woman abode, and gave her son suck until she weaned him.

verses.text_plain: And when she had weaned him, she took him up with her, with three bullocks, and one ephah of flour, and a bottle of wine, and brought him unto the house of the Lord in Shiloh: and the child was young.
verses.verse_html: 24And when she had weaned him, she took him up with her, with three bullocks, and one ephah of flour, and a bottle of wine, and brought him unto the house of the Lord in Shiloh: and the child was young.

verses.text_plain: And they slew a bullock, and brought the child to Eli.
verses.verse_html: 25And they slew a bullock, and brought the child to Eli.

verses.text_plain: And she said, Oh my lord, as thy soul liveth, my lord, I am the woman that stood by thee here, praying unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 26And she said, Oh my lord, as thy soul liveth, my lord, I am the woman that stood by thee here, praying unto the Lord.

verses.text_plain: For this child I prayed; and the Lord hath given me my petition which I asked of him:
verses.verse_html: 27For this child I prayed; and the Lord hath given me my petition which I asked of him:

verses.text_plain: Therefore also I have lent him to the Lord; as long as he liveth he shall be lent to the Lord. And he worshipped the Lord there.
verses.verse_html:
28Therefore also I have lent him to the Lord; as long as he liveth he shall be lent to the Lord. And he worshipped the Lord there. ▼
▼ lent him: or, returned him, whom I have obtained by petition
 , ▼
▼ he shall…: or, he whom I have obtained by petition shall be returned
